1. Prepare 
1.1 host machine
A user
ssh keys
1.2 cluster machine
authorization keys for the user
docker 
user in docker group

2. Generate rke yml config file

3. Run rke to start cluster

4. Install kubectl 

5. add config for kubectl

6. validate kube cluster is running 
```
$ kubectl cluster-info
Kubernetes master is running at https://xserattd002:6443
CoreDNS is running at https://xserattd002:6443/api/v1/namespaces/kube-system/services/kube-dns:dns/proxy

To further debug and diagnose cluster problems, use 'kubectl cluster-info dump'.
```
7. deploy a hello world 
